args:
As the prince and his comrades march on,
they are beset by a black fog. As it dissipates,
they find themselves lost inside the palace.
Separated from their forces, they steel their
resolve and make their way through the fiend-
filled depths to a confrontation with the Other.
It is enshrouded in a dense fog\nwith an ominous aura.
Easy, friends—I dispatched these men\nto scout out the situation at the palace.\n...Well? How are the Other's defenses?
Deserted, sir. We didn't see signs of\neven a single enemy solider.

I ain't the sharpest blade in the rack,
but Ranzal's ma didn't raise a kid
dumb enough to believe the Other
is just sittin' in there all alone.
Yeah, this smells like an ambush.
Right, but an ambush from WHERE?\nThere's no place for soldiers to be\nhiding between here and the palace.
Scanning for magical devices...\nNegative. No devices found.
Meaning we can rule out any more\nsurprises like that from Harle.
All we can do now is keep moving\nand make sure we're careful.
Understood, Your Highness. ...All units,\nadvance—and be ready for anything!
I almost can't believe it, but there\ntruly are no enemies here.
And I don't get the sense they're waiting\nup ahead, either. Still, it's strange...
No matter how much we walk, it doesn't\nseem like we're getting any closer.
Let's all just take a deep breath, yeah?\nWe've been walkin' for a while now—\nwe HAVE to be closer!
The prince is correct: I am detecting\nerrors with our location data.
Look out! The fog is growing thicker!
I can't see my own hand\nin front of my face!
Everyone, grab the person next to you\nand don't let go! We'll move as one!
Hey, over there! It's the palace!
We couldn't approach it before,\nso why can we do so now?
Perhaps we are meant to take it as an\ninvitation. Shall we do so, Highness?
It could be dangerous, but we can't\nstop now. Let's go!
Good news is, we made it inside.\nBAD news is, we lost all the soldiers\nwhat we came here with.
Looks like the gate locked behind us,\nso you can forget turning around and\ntrying to find 'em.
Why did our group—and ONLY ours—\nmanage to make it inside?
It's like the Other wants us to come.
Make no mistake: Morsayati DOES\nhave some kind of reason for this.
So if we're going to get out,\nwe'll have to defeat him first.
Numerous fiends detected in the vicinity.\nThey are approaching our position.\nPrepare for combat.
And here I thought we might just be\nable to waltz inside and settle this.
Let's head for the throne room and take\ndown these fiends in the process!
